\code{process_chunk(text, done)}; the final call usually has \code{text = NULL} and
\code{done = TRUE}.
\item \strong{thinking} -- a reasoning stream bracketed by \code{start_thinking()}
and \code{stop_thinking()}.
\item \strong{tools} -- tool execution: \code{render_tool_start(name, arguments)}
followed by \code{render_tool_result(name, result, success, raw_result)}.
\item \strong{steps} -- multi-step ReAct loop boundaries, \code{reset_for_new_step()}.
}

Every method is a no-op in the base class, so the base class is itself a usable
null renderer and a subclass need only override the events it cares about.
